==English==

===Etymology===
Named after the industrial chemist Ernst Büchner.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[Büchner]] [[flask]]}}

# {{context|chemistry|lang=en}} A type of glass [[flask]] used in a [[laboratory]] similar to an [[Erlenmeyer flask]], but with a side spout used for connection to an [[aspirator]].

